<L>__{exterior street day}
<A>__{mother and son walking together.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{my mother was the most beautiful women of her day. but if she was proud of her beauty, to do her justice, she was still more proud of her son, and has said a thousand times to me that i was the handsomest fellow in the world.}
<L>__{exterior church day}
<A>__{mother and son entering church.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{the good soul's pleasure was to dress me; and on sundays and holidays, i turned out in a velvet coat with a silver hilted sword by my side, and a gold garter at my knee as fine as any lord in the land. as we walked to church on sundays, even the most envious souls would allow that there was not a prettier pair in the kingdom.}
